{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":11544,"text":"So what does it mean\nfor a machine to be athletic?"},{"time":15059,"text":"We will demonstrate the concept\nof machine athleticism"},{"time":17908,"text":"and the research to achieve it"},{"time":19628,"text":"with the help of these flying machines\ncalled quadrocopters,"},{"time":22510,"text":"or quads, for short."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26291,"text":"Quads have been around for a long time."},{"time":28501,"text":"They're so popular these days\nbecause they're mechanically simple."},{"time":32255,"text":"By controlling\nthe speeds of these four propellers,"},{"time":34668,"text":"these machines can roll, pitch, yaw,"},{"time":37437,"text":"and accelerate\nalong their common orientation."},{"time":40179,"text":"On board are also a battery, a computer,"},{"time":43401,"text":"various sensors and wireless radios."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47298,"text":"Quads are extremely agile,\nbut this agility comes at a cost."},{"time":51762,"text":"They are inherently unstable,"},{"time":53874,"text":"and they need some form\nof automatic feedback control"},{"time":56469,"text":"in order to be able to fly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64259,"text":"So, how did it just do that?"},{"time":67497,"text":"Cameras on the ceiling and a laptop"},{"time":69315,"text":"serve as an indoor\nglobal positioning system."},{"time":72301,"text":"It's used to locate objects in the space"},{"time":74364,"text":"that have these reflective\nmarkers on them."},{"time":76476,"text":"This data is then sent to another laptop"},{"time":78538,"text":"that is running estimation\nand control algorithms,"},{"time":80920,"text":"which in turn sends commands to the quad,"},{"time":82898,"text":"which is also running estimation\nand control algorithms."},{"time":89864,"text":"The bulk of our research is algorithms."},{"time":92130,"text":"It's the magic that brings\nthese machines to life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96291,"text":"So how does one design the algorithms\nthat create a machine athlete?"},{"time":100792,"text":"We use something broadly\ncalled model-based design."},{"time":103839,"text":"We first capture the physics"},{"time":105229,"text":"with a mathematical model\nof how the machines behave."},{"time":108636,"text":"We then use a branch of mathematics\ncalled control theory"},{"time":112610,"text":"to analyze these models"},{"time":114291,"text":"and also to synthesize\nalgorithms for controlling them."},{"time":117820,"text":"For example, that's how we can\nmake the quad hover."},{"time":120868,"text":"We first captured the dynamics\nwith a set of differential equations."},{"time":124182,"text":"We then manipulate these equations\nwith the help of control theory"},{"time":127658,"text":"to create algorithms\nthat stabilize the quad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131130,"text":"Let me demonstrate\nthe strength of this approach."},{"time":137198,"text":"Suppose that we want\nthis quad to not only hover"},{"time":139855,"text":"but to also balance this pole."},{"time":142520,"text":"With a little bit of practice,"},{"time":144318,"text":"it's pretty straightforward\nfor a human being to do this,"},{"time":147025,"text":"although we do have the advantage\nof having two feet on the ground"},{"time":150240,"text":"and the use of our very versatile hands."},{"time":152804,"text":"It becomes a little bit more difficult"},{"time":155566,"text":"when I only have one foot on the ground"},{"time":157569,"text":"and when I don't use my hands."},{"time":160733,"text":"Notice how this pole has\na reflective marker on top,"},{"time":163319,"text":"which means that it can\nbe located in the space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172276,"text":"(Audience) Oh!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":173367,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":177695,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179387,"text":"You can notice that this quad\nis making fine adjustments"},{"time":182052,"text":"to keep the pole balanced."},{"time":184417,"text":"How did we design\nthe algorithms to do this?"},{"time":187027,"text":"We added the mathematical\nmodel of the pole"},{"time":189132,"text":"to that of the quad."},{"time":190603,"text":"Once we have a model\nof the combined quad-pole system,"},{"time":193605,"text":"we can use control theory to create\nalgorithms for controlling it."},{"time":198538,"text":"Here, you see that it's stable,"},{"time":200126,"text":"and even if I give it little nudges,"},{"time":202819,"text":"it goes back --"},{"time":205589,"text":"to the nice, balanced position."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208087,"text":"We can also augment the model"},{"time":209501,"text":"to include where we want\nthe quad to be in space."},{"time":212428,"text":"Using this pointer,\nmade out of reflective markers,"},{"time":215395,"text":"I can point to where I want\nthe quad to be in space"},{"time":217848,"text":"a fixed distance away from me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227785,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":235763,"text":"The key to these acrobatic\nmaneuvers is algorithms,"},{"time":238913,"text":"designed with the help\nof mathematical models"},{"time":241230,"text":"and control theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243246,"text":"Let's tell the quad to come back here"},{"time":245255,"text":"and let the pole drop,"},{"time":246943,"text":"and I will next demonstrate the importance"},{"time":249098,"text":"of understanding physical models"},{"time":251111,"text":"and the workings of the physical world."},{"time":265462,"text":"Notice how the quad lost altitude\nwhen I put this glass of water on it."},{"time":269314,"text":"Unlike the balancing pole,"},{"time":270741,"text":"I did not include the mathematical\nmodel of the glass"},{"time":273780,"text":"in the system."},{"time":275111,"text":"In fact, the system doesn't even know\nthat the glass is there."},{"time":278148,"text":"Like before, I could use\nthe pointer to tell the quad"},{"time":280910,"text":"where I want it to be in space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285684,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":291531,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293515,"text":"Okay, you should be asking yourself,"},{"time":295278,"text":"why doesn't the water\nfall out of the glass?"},{"time":297888,"text":"Two facts."},{"time":298942,"text":"The first is that gravity acts\non all objects in the same way."},{"time":303051,"text":"The second is that the propellers"},{"time":304854,"text":"are all pointing in the same direction\nof the glass, pointing up."},{"time":308642,"text":"You put these two things together,"},{"time":310313,"text":"the net result is that all side forces\non the glass are small"},{"time":313892,"text":"and are mainly dominated\nby aerodynamic effects,"},{"time":316193,"text":"which at these speeds are negligible."},{"time":323336,"text":"And that's why you don't need\nto model the glass."},{"time":325694,"text":"It naturally doesn't spill,\nno matter what the quad does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332500,"text":"(Audience) Oh!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338340,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":343159,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345940,"text":"The lesson here"},{"time":347078,"text":"is that some high-performance tasks\nare easier than others,"},{"time":351115,"text":"and that understanding\nthe physics of the problem"},{"time":353476,"text":"tells you which ones are easy\nand which ones are hard."},{"time":356194,"text":"In this instance, carrying\na glass of water is easy."},{"time":358728,"text":"Balancing a pole is hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362171,"text":"We've all heard stories of athletes\nperforming feats while physically injured."},{"time":366466,"text":"Can a machine also perform\nwith extreme physical damage?"},{"time":370636,"text":"Conventional wisdom says"},{"time":372145,"text":"that you need at least four fixed motor\npropeller pairs in order to fly,"},{"time":376052,"text":"because there are four degrees\nof freedom to control:"},{"time":378600,"text":"roll, pitch, yaw and acceleration."},{"time":381192,"text":"Hexacopters and octocopters,\nwith six and eight propellers,"},{"time":384437,"text":"can provide redundancy,"},{"time":385920,"text":"but quadrocopters are much more popular"},{"time":387909,"text":"because they have the minimum number\nof fixed motor propeller pairs: four."},{"time":392168,"text":"Or do they?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":400827,"text":"(Audience) Oh!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":402407,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":409334,"text":"If we analyze the mathematical\nmodel of this machine"},{"time":412076,"text":"with only two working propellers,"},{"time":414252,"text":"we discover that there's\nan unconventional way to fly it."},{"time":427980,"text":"We relinquish control of yaw,"},{"time":429686,"text":"but roll, pitch and acceleration\ncan still be controlled"},{"time":432756,"text":"with algorithms that exploit\nthis new configuration."},{"time":441668,"text":"Mathematical models tell us\nexactly when and why this is possible."},{"time":445981,"text":"In this instance, this knowledge\nallows us to design"},{"time":448783,"text":"novel machine architectures"},{"time":451280,"text":"or to design clever algorithms\nthat gracefully handle damage,"},{"time":454972,"text":"just like human athletes do,"},{"time":456696,"text":"instead of building\nmachines with redundancy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460688,"text":"We can't help but hold our breath"},{"time":462369,"text":"when we watch a diver\nsomersaulting into the water,"},{"time":465068,"text":"or when a vaulter is twisting in the air,"},{"time":467045,"text":"the ground fast approaching."},{"time":468576,"text":"Will the diver be able\nto pull off a rip entry?"},{"time":471144,"text":"Will the vaulter stick the landing?"},{"time":473292,"text":"Suppose we want this quad here\nto perform a triple flip"},{"time":476496,"text":"and finish off at the exact same\nspot that it started."},{"time":479736,"text":"This maneuver is going\nto happen so quickly"},{"time":481879,"text":"that we can't use position feedback\nto correct the motion during execution."},{"time":485748,"text":"There simply isn't enough time."},{"time":487782,"text":"Instead, what the quad can do\nis perform the maneuver blindly,"},{"time":491476,"text":"observe how it finishes the maneuver,"},{"time":493708,"text":"and then use that information\nto modify its behavior"},{"time":496209,"text":"so that the next flip is better."},{"time":498421,"text":"Similar to the diver and the vaulter,"},{"time":500233,"text":"it is only through repeated practice"},{"time":502152,"text":"that the maneuver can\nbe learned and executed"},{"time":504319,"text":"to the highest standard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513100,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514393,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":519164,"text":"Striking a moving ball\nis a necessary skill in many sports."},{"time":523127,"text":"How do we make a machine do"},{"time":524643,"text":"what an athlete does\nseemingly without effort?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537547,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":544143,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":548500,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550542,"text":"This quad has a racket\nstrapped onto its head"},{"time":553192,"text":"with a sweet spot roughly the size\nof an apple, so not too large."},{"time":557017,"text":"The following calculations\nare made every 20 milliseconds,"},{"time":559846,"text":"or 50 times per second."},{"time":561602,"text":"We first figure out where\nthe ball is going."},{"time":564414,"text":"We then next calculate\nhow the quad should hit the ball"},{"time":567059,"text":"so that it flies\nto where it was thrown from."},{"time":569950,"text":"Third, a trajectory is planned\nthat carries the quad"},{"time":574406,"text":"from its current state\nto the impact point with the ball."},{"time":577430,"text":"Fourth, we only execute 20 milliseconds'\nworth of that strategy."},{"time":581366,"text":"Twenty milliseconds later,\nthe whole process is repeated"},{"time":584183,"text":"until the quad strikes the ball."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595290,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598131,"text":"Machines can not only perform\ndynamic maneuvers on their own,"},{"time":601578,"text":"they can do it collectively."},{"time":603441,"text":"These three quads are cooperatively\ncarrying a sky net."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615589,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":620372,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621985,"text":"They perform an extremely dynamic\nand collective maneuver"},{"time":626350,"text":"to launch the ball back to me."},{"time":628042,"text":"Notice that, at full extension,\nthese quads are vertical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636486,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":638258,"text":"In fact, when fully extended,"},{"time":640425,"text":"this is roughly five times greater\nthan what a bungee jumper feels"},{"time":643712,"text":"at the end of their launch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651203,"text":"The algorithms to do this are very similar"},{"time":653686,"text":"to what the single quad used\nto hit the ball back to me."},{"time":657070,"text":"Mathematical models are used\nto continuously re-plan"},{"time":659934,"text":"a cooperative strategy\n50 times per second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664506,"text":"Everything we have seen so far has been\nabout the machines and their capabilities."},{"time":668789,"text":"What happens when we couple\nthis machine athleticism"},{"time":671805,"text":"with that of a human being?"},{"time":673765,"text":"What I have in front of me\nis a commercial gesture sensor"},{"time":677385,"text":"mainly used in gaming."},{"time":678694,"text":"It can recognize\nwhat my various body parts"},{"time":680766,"text":"are doing in real time."},{"time":682710,"text":"Similar to the pointer\nthat I used earlier,"},{"time":684813,"text":"we can use this as inputs to the system."},{"time":687454,"text":"We now have a natural way of interacting"},{"time":689850,"text":"with the raw athleticism\nof these quads with my gestures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730715,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":744354,"text":"Interaction doesn't have to be virtual."},{"time":746394,"text":"It can be physical."},{"time":747989,"text":"Take this quad, for example."},{"time":749893,"text":"It's trying to stay\nat a fixed point in space."},{"time":752933,"text":"If I try to move it\nout of the way, it fights me,"},{"time":756646,"text":"and moves back to where it wants to be."},{"time":760254,"text":"We can change this behavior, however."},{"time":763373,"text":"We can use mathematical models"},{"time":765072,"text":"to estimate the force\nthat I'm applying to the quad."},{"time":768205,"text":"Once we know this force,\nwe can also change the laws of physics,"},{"time":771443,"text":"as far as the quad\nis concerned, of course."},{"time":775942,"text":"Here, the quad is behaving\nas if it were in a viscous fluid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782570,"text":"We now have an intimate way\nof interacting with a machine."},{"time":786593,"text":"I will use this new capability to position"},{"time":789099,"text":"this camera-carrying quad\nto the appropriate location"},{"time":791676,"text":"for filming the remainder\nof this demonstration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804583,"text":"So we can physically interact\nwith these quads"},{"time":806990,"text":"and we can change the laws of physics."},{"time":809393,"text":"Let's have a little bit of fun with this."},{"time":811539,"text":"For what you will see next,"},{"time":812932,"text":"these quads will initially behave\nas if they were on Pluto."},{"time":816906,"text":"As time goes on, gravity will be increased"},{"time":819218,"text":"until we're all back on planet Earth,"},{"time":821267,"text":"but I assure you we won't get there."},{"time":823462,"text":"Okay, here goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832897,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":862778,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":865858,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":869760,"text":"Whew!"},{"time":875045,"text":"You're all thinking now,"},{"time":876296,"text":"these guys are having way too much fun,"},{"time":878271,"text":"and you're probably also asking yourself,"},{"time":880350,"text":"why exactly are they building\nmachine athletes?"},{"time":884286,"text":"Some conjecture that the role\nof play in the animal kingdom"},{"time":887120,"text":"is to hone skills\nand develop capabilities."},{"time":889690,"text":"Others think that it has\nmore of a social role,"},{"time":891929,"text":"that it's used to bind the group."},{"time":893603,"text":"Similarly, we use the analogy\nof sports and athleticism"},{"time":896963,"text":"to create new algorithms for machines"},{"time":899042,"text":"to push them to their limits."},{"time":901350,"text":"What impact will the speed\nof machines have on our way of life?"},{"time":904866,"text":"Like all our past creations\nand innovations,"},{"time":907255,"text":"they may be used to improve\nthe human condition"},{"time":910082,"text":"or they may be misused and abused."},{"time":912595,"text":"This is not a technical choice\nwe are faced with;"},{"time":914921,"text":"it's a social one."},{"time":916332,"text":"Let's make the right choice,"},{"time":917707,"text":"the choice that brings out the best\nin the future of machines,"},{"time":920643,"text":"just like athleticism in sports\ncan bring out the best in us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924380,"text":"Let me introduce you to the wizards\nbehind the green curtain."},{"time":927479,"text":"They're the current members\nof the Flying Machine Arena research team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930837,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":935267,"text":"Federico Augugliaro, Dario Brescianini,"},{"time":937569,"text":"Markus Hehn, Sergei Lupashin,\nMark Muller and Robin Ritz."},{"time":941018,"text":"Look out for them.\nThey're destined for great things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943566,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944644,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}